# Rust backend (Tauri)

## Format & lint

- Format with **rustfmt** (defaults; no `rustfmt.toml` in repo): `pnpm format:rust` or `cargo fmt --manifest-path src-tauri/Cargo.toml`.
- Prefer `cargo clippy` before large changes; fix new warnings when reasonable.

## Layout

- New commands go under `src-tauri/src/commands/` and are registered from `lib.rs`.
- Keep **Tauri command handlers** thin: parse inputs, call helpers, return `Result`—avoid `unwrap()`/`expect()` on user-facing paths unless documented.

## macOS / AppKit

- **AppKit and Accessibility (AX) work must run on the main thread** (`run_on_main_thread` / patterns already used in this codebase). Do not call UI/AX APIs from arbitrary threads.

## Errors

- Return `Result<T, String>` (or a serializable error type) from `#[tauri::command]` functions; propagate with `?` where types align.

## Examples

```rust
// ❌ BAD — AX from a random thread
std::thread::spawn(|| { /* get_selected_text */ });

// ✅ GOOD — dispatch to main, then do AX / NSWorkspace work
run_on_main_thread(|| { /* ... */ });
```

```rust
// ❌ BAD
let x = risky_operation().unwrap();

// ✅ GOOD
let x = risky_operation().map_err(|e| e.to_string())?;
```
